_source.title: [INSPIRE] Country fiche / header
_source.visState:
{"title":"[INSPIRE] Country fiche / header","type":"markdown","params":{"markdown":"![INSPIRE](../../assets/img/logo_inspire_150.png)
# Status of implementation of the INSPIRE Directive – Country Fiches

The INSPIRE Directive sets the minimum conditions for interoperable sharing and exchange of spatial data across Europe as part of a larger European Interoperability Framework and the e-Government Action Plan that contributes to the Digital Single Market Agenda. Article 21 of [INSPIRE Directive](http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=CELEX:32007L0002:EN:NOT) defines the basic principles for monitoring and reporting. More detailed implementing rules regarding INSPIRE monitoring and reporting have been adopted as [COMMISSION DECISION regarding INSPIRE monitoring and reporting](http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=OJ:L:2009:148:0018:0026:EN:PDF) on the 5th of June 2009.


This country fiche highlights the progress in member states in the various areas of INSPIRE implementation and presents an outlook of planned actions for further improvement of the INSPIRE implementation. The country fiche is a summary of the information acquired through: 
* the tri-annual INSPIRE implementation report,
* the monitoring report in May, 
* a bilateral written exchange on the implementation of the INSPIRE Directive between the Commission and member state representatives."},"aggs":[],"listeners":{}}

_source.title: [INSPIRE] Country fiche / key facts
_source.visState:
{"title":"[INSPIRE] Country fiche / key facts","type":"markdown","params":{"markdown":"## Key Facts and Figures

In addition to the above mentioned issues, the implementation of INSPIRE Directive requires Member States to take four main steps in relation to management of spatial datasets which fall under the Directive: 
* Step 1: Identify spatial datasets
* Step 2: Document these datasets (metadata)
* Step 3: Provide services for identified spatial datasets (discovery, view, download)
* Step 4: Make spatial datasets interoperable by aligning them with the common data models. 

The key facts and figures presented in this country fiche are based on the information provided by the member state on the [INSPIRE dashboard](https://inspire-dashboard.eea.europa.eu/). The provided statistics is not reflecting the data available on [INSPIRE geoportal](http://inspire-geoportal.ec.europa.eu/).

The conformity of the implementation is assessed against the full set of legal specifications set out by the Directive and the Implementing Rules and the commonly agreed good practices set out by the technical guidelines.

### Identification of spatial data with relevance to the environment (step 1)"},"aggs":[],"listeners":{}}
